OL,3,C'Trapped in a home I can't sell':
OL,4,CResident's plea as cladding causes
OL,5,Cfire hazard
OL,7,F"If a fire starts on the other side of
OL,8,Fthe building, then I'm told my home is
OL,9,Fin trouble. Every day I'm told I'm
OL,10,Fliving in a building that's high risk."
OL,12,FLucy bought her two-bed flat with the
OL,13,Fformer government's Help to Buy
OL,14,Fscheme. Now she's paying back #100 a
OL,15,Fmonth in interest on the loan for a
OL,16,Fproperty she can't sell because no
OL,17,Fmortgage company will lend against it.
